title: Taiwan Air Force Loses Second Jet Fighter This Year
sub_head: Crash comes as the war in Ukraine intensifies concerns about Taiwan’s ability to defend itself against China
body:
TAIPEI—A Taiwanese jet fighter plunged into the sea on Monday, the second such incident this year and seventh since the start of 2020.
Taiwan’s air force said the pilot ejected from his Mirage 2000 aircraft in a parachute at 11:26 a.m. local time, more than an hour after it took off on a combat training mission from an airfield in the eastern county of Taitung.
